{"first_name":"Martin","last_name":"Diessner","permalink":"martin-diessner","crunchbase_url":"http://www.crunchbase.com/person/martin-diessner","homepage_url":"http://www.martindiessner.com","birthplace":"Leipzig","twitter_username":"martindiessner","blog_url":"http://blog.martindiessner.com","blog_feed_url":"","affiliation_name":"Adidas","born_year":1975,"born_month":2,"born_day":27,"tag_list":"","alias_list":null,"created_at":"Tue Mar 17 05:09:54 UTC 2009","updated_at":"Tue Feb 14 03:31:26 UTC 2012","overview":"<p>Martin grew up in Leipzig, Eastern Germany and later on studied International Management with focus on Finance and Marketing at Bradford&#8217;s Management Center. He also has a Master&#8217;s degree in Computer Science from London&#8217;s City University.</p>\n\n<p>His career started with a stint at Daimler Chrysler&#8217;s research and development division, before moving over to the sports company adidas, where he held various positions at adidas Germany, Europe and Global Marketing.</p>\n\n<p>Martin moved to the United Arab Emirates end of 2001 where he worked as Business Development Manager for the regional advertising group BBDO in the Middle East.</p>\n\n<p>In 2004, with his business partner Dinesh Lalvani, he co-founded and setup Flip Media which later became the leading digital media and marketing company across the Middle East. </p>\n\n<p>In December 2006, HSBC Private Equity Middle East Ltd. acquired a significant equity stake in Flip Holding which was subsequently sold to Publicis Groupe (PUB.PA).</p>\n\n<p>In 2008, Martin retired from the day-to-day operation of the business. Together with his wife, they spend the majority of their time traveling between Dubai, Europe and South Africa.</p>\n\n<p>Martin has a great passion for everything digital, entrepreneurial business ideas and technical gadgets. He is a keen sportsman (running and cycling his favorites) and also loves playing piano.</p>","image":{"available_sizes":[[[150,150],"assets/image